snippet.textDisplay: Actually my family won the N64 in a Taco Bell sweepstakes. we were so broke but we really wanted it. :D The deal was that whenever u buy medium sodas at TB you would get Nintendo themed cups. UNDER the cup you would get one of the faces of these four characters: DK, Yoshi, Luigi, and Mario. DK didn't get u anything, and it went up in rewards from taco and food to the rare mario getting you a N64 with this game. anyone remember that? i was 5 or 6 then :D

snippet.textDisplay: This is the single game that had the biggest impact on my gaming years. I have never been more hyped for a game than Super Mario 64. I'd look at screenshots in magazines and dream of being able to play the game someday. When my parents brought home a brand new N64 with this game, I pretty much had the same reaction as the N64 kid. Controlling Mario for the first time outside the castle is something I'll never forget, it was magical. And I know it was for a lot of you as well.
